      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (fluid viscosity, hematocrit, temperature, inlet flow waveform) documented with measurement uncertainty. Blood analog (glycerol-water) used in place of whole blood; viscosity matched to ±2% at 37°C. Hematocrit variability ±3% documented. Confidence rated LOW due to blood analog substitution uncertainty; residual risk accepted because hemolysis power-law sensitivity to viscosity is bounded by parametric sweep in UQ record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
