      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) in g/100L, directly mapped to clinical hemolysis threshold per ISO 10993-4. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time histogram) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis damage model. Relevance chain documented. Confidence rated MODERATE; acknowledged that NIH is a surrogate for in-vivo hemolysis and extrapolation uncertainty is non-negligible but bounded."
